      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SOKAI (7) was checked in the run and safely held when sixth (31.53) in a Grade 6 over 530m at Angle Park. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Has the ability and looks hard to top. HELD FOR RANSOM (4) has a strong winning strike-rate over this journey with three wins and a placing from six tries. Comes off a (17.55) win last time, scoring by 2.75 lengths in a Grade 6 over 305m at Mt Gambier. Looks suited here and can measure up. ROUGH GIRL RUBY (1) has some solid form under her belt and proved too classy last time to win by 0.8 lengths at Mt Gambier in a handy 17.73 beating Duran Rachel. Winner at her latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. One of main contenders. KILCOY LASS (2) placed last time out at big odds - worth considering.",
